"Invasive Mechanical Ventilation"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s22_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Indications"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b670b8",
"children":[
"Indications"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bcf26d",
"children":[
"Patients may require invasive mechanical ventilatory support for hypoxemic respiratory failure (low arterial P",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"O"
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
") or hypercapnic ventilatory failure (increased arterial P",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"CO"
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"). The indications for invasive mechanical ventilation are hypoxemic or hypercapnic respiratory failure, contraindication to ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"noninvasive positive-pressure ventilation",
"children":[
"NPPV"
]
},
","
]
},
" and inability to protect the airway."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_pm_s22_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fe4605",
"children":[
"Difficult ventilation or complications of mechanical ventilation resulting from changes in airway resistance may first be manifested by an increase in the peak inspiratory pressure alone, resulting from:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ac4c72",
"children":[
"bronchospasm"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"011087",
"children":[
"secretions in airways, endotracheal tube, or ventilator tubing"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b58c46",
"children":[
"obstructing mucus plug"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0da570",
"children":[
"agitation with dyssynchrony with the ventilator"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3beeff",
"children":[
"When a patient can maintain an arterial O",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" saturation >90% breathing F",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"IO"
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" ≤0.5, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"positive end-expiratory pressure",
"children":[
"PEEP"
]
},
" <5 cm H",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"O, and pH >7.30, it is reasonable to consider extubation. Paired daily spontaneous awakening trials (withdrawal of sedatives) with daily spontaneous breathing trials result in a reduction in mechanical ventilation time, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"intensive care unit",
"children":[
"ICU"
]
},
" and hospital length of stay, and 1-year mortality rates."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c5bafd",
"children":[
"Do not select synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation as a weaning mode, because studies have demonstrated it actually takes longer to liberate patients from the ventilator."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s22_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"dcc290",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 73-year-old woman who weighs 56 kg (123 lb) is admitted to the ICU with an exacerbation of severe ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"chronic obstructive pulmonary disease",
"children":[
"COPD"
]
},
"."
]
},
" Intubation and mechanical ventilation are required: F",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"small",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"IO"
]
},
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
" of 0.4, tidal volume of 450 mL, and respiration rate of 16/min. Thirty minutes later, her ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"blood pressure",
"children":[
"BP"
]
},
" has dropped to 82/60 mm Hg. She is restless and has diffuse wheezing with prolonged expiration."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"52242f",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose auto-PEEP. For management, select treatment of airway obstruction."
]
}
]
}
]
},
